EXTRACTED VALUE: "I am an old man who will live until I die," Anselmo said. "And I am not afraid of foxes."
Catalina hesitated for a moment, hearing the proud ring of certainty, a determination to match her own mother's voice.
"I am no mean advocate, I can plead my case."
She bent to the diagram once again, then jabbed her finger at the southeast corner of the church. "She's there. With Mère Aurélie."
He shuff led through them. "Christ. What is this shit?"
